## Quick Exercise

Choose a project you're working on. Write three adjectives for its personality. Then look at your current UI: does each element express those adjectives? Find the one most inconsistent element and fix it.

Before building any UI, fill this out:

```
Product: ___________
Adjectives: _____, _____, _____
Shape direction: rounded / sharp / mixed
Color temp: warm / cool / neutral
Typeface mood: casual / neutral / authoritative
Density: airy / moderate / dense
```

Pin this somewhere visible while you design.

## Quick Recap (Because We'll Forget)

- Personality is a set of consistent signals, not decoration.
- Four levers: shape, color temperature, typeface mood, density.
- Pick adjectives first, then tune levers to match.
- Inconsistency breaks personality harder than any single bad choice.
